      "comment": "SWEET ROSE (5) was good from the front at Nowra in soggy conditions a month ago, beaten 0.9L. Should be prominent from the outset again with a favourable draw. Given plenty of time to get over her debut and she creates interest with improvement likely. THE WAY AHEAD (6) is usually in the finish and can feature again with Boudvillain on board back to Country level. RUSSIAN REIGN (2) has to be included off a solid return effort at Gosford. That effort rates strongly in this field and with improvement likely, he'll be right in the finish. TERRA LUMINA (3) will be fitter for a couple of trials coming into this and has shown glimpses of talent early in his career. He looks the next best.",
